    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-03-10T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-03-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="223"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d223">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Captain <persName type="from">Stubbs</persName> to Mr.
                            <persName type="to">Gresham</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">New York</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-03-10">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 10, 1894</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Has there been any settlement or attempt to settle on the part of the Government
                    of Santo Domingo for the injuries to schooner <hi rend="italic">Henry
                        Crosby</hi> and crew, at Azua, December 10? Please wire reply care Smith,
                    Gregory &amp; Winters, New York.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">A. F. Stubbs</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Master Schooner Henry Crosby</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
